caption: Purchases Requiring Competitive Quotation Process
created: 20260405120000000
modified: 20260405120000000
title: Policy3330(IV)(1)
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Price quotations should be requested for all purchases of goods or general services, including high technology equipment, expected to involve an expenditure of at least $15,000 but less than $34,999.99. Purchases of goods or services that involve an expenditure of less than $15,000 may be made directly, without regard to any competitive bid or quotation process. Waivers from the quotation process are available for the same reasons that Waivers are available from the bidding process. (See Section V.)
